XDescription
X     Here's another calendar program which I think is considerably more
X     useful than pcal.  For starters, the calendars really do occupy a full
X     line-printer page; they also include small calendars for the previous
X     and subsequent months along with a month/year heading in 5x9
X     dot-matrix characters, printed with overstrikes (on line printers
X     capable of handling them).  Options are available to select:
X
X     Calen prints a full size wall calendar suitable for printing on
X     14" wide paper in 10 characters per inch.
X
X     Originally written in FORTRAN-IV for GE Timesharing, 10/65
